quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,118,"And those who have no knowledge say: "
  2,119,"Verily, We have sent you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) with the truth (Islâm), a bringer of glad tidings (for those who believe in what you brought, that they will enter Paradise) and a warner (for those who disbelieve in what you brought, that they will enter the Hell-fire).{1} And you will not be asked about the dwellers of the blazing Fire.",1:[{2:119} See the footnote of {3:85}]
  2,120,"Never will the Jews nor the Christians be pleased with you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) till you follow their religion. Say: "
  3,58,"This is what We recite to you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) of the Verses and the Wise Reminder (i.e. the Qur’ân)."
  3,59,"Verily, the likeness of ‘Îsâ (Jesus) before Allâh is the likeness of Adam. He created him from dust, then (He) said to him: "
  3,60,"(This is) the truth from your Lord, so be not of those who doubt."